@startuml state-fund-health
title Fund Financial Governance -- Fund Health States

skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor<<healthy>> #d4edda
  BackgroundColor<<caution>> #fff3cd
  BackgroundColor<<critical>> #f8d7da
}

[*] --> Healthy

state "Healthy" as Healthy <<healthy>> {
  Healthy : Reserve ratio >= 3 months
  Healthy : All payout caps normal
  Healthy : No restrictions
}

state "Caution" as Caution <<caution>> {
  Caution : Reserve ratio 1-3 months
  Caution : Admin notified
  Caution : Payout review expedited
  Caution : Contribution increase suggested
}

state "Critical" as Critical <<critical>> {
  Critical : Reserve ratio < 1 month
  Critical : Board notified immediately
  Critical : Payouts require board approval
  Critical : Emergency contribution appeal
  Critical : Payout caps may be reduced
}

Healthy --> Caution : Reserve ratio\ndrops below 3 months
Caution --> Healthy : Reserve ratio\nrecovers to >= 3 months
Caution --> Critical : Reserve ratio\ndrops below 1 month
Critical --> Caution : Reserve ratio\nrecovers to >= 1 month

note right of Healthy
  **Reserve Ratio** =
  Reserve Balance /
  Avg Monthly Payouts (6-month window)
end note

note right of Critical
  In Critical state, the system:
  1. Blocks new non-emergency payouts
  2. Sends urgent alerts to all admins
  3. Logs state transition in audit trail
end note

@enduml
